title: Shooting Star/Spiderweb by Robert Bloch
description:
Part of the Hard Case Crime series of books, this volume contains two complete novels by the renowned Robert Bloch.

"Shooting Star:" When murder comes to Hollywood, only a one-eyed private eye can spot the killer. The story was first published by Ace Books in 1958.
"Spiderweb:" Even a phony fortune teller could see danger in her fortune. The story was first published by Ace Books in 1954.

The Hard Case Crime series recreates, in editorial form and content, the style of the paperback crime novels of the 1940s and '50s. The covers feature original art done in the pulp style.

Genre: Mystery
